title: Ask HN: Space for Vanilla JavaScript and Serverless?
text:
Hello! Wondering where else can this stack fit. I (and some colleagues) have been exposed mostly to vanilla JS for library-like component construction and usage, and also running JS scripts in serverless environments (Netlify, Azure Functions).

So no traditional React/Postgre/Next etc knowledge.

Where can I take these skills and put them to good use? I thought about constructing API's and placing them on RapidAPI or similar.

Tell HN: WhatsApp getting slower on macOS despite “performance improvements”
text:
Every update description says "bug fixes and performance improvements". Yet, WhatsApp has gotten slower over time on my M1 Pro Macbook Pro. I see more loading screens, more stutters, more jitters.

Is the update description lying? Maybe it should say "bug fixes and performance degradation".
